  "prompt": "What does mah mean on mobile battery?",
  "response": "\"mAh\" stands for milliampere-hour and is a unit used to measure the energy capacity of a battery. It is commonly used to denote the storage capacity of batteries in mobile phones and other electronic devices. The higher the mAh rating, the more energy the battery can store, which typically means it can power the device for a longer period of time before needing to be recharged. For example, a battery rated at 3000 mAh can theoretically deliver 3000 milliamperes of current for one hour, or 1000 milliamperes for three hours, and so on.",
